From 8aaeb262fd07e7708913a95a3f246f91f723d737 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Guillaume Ausset <guillaume@ausset.me>
Date: Fri, 13 Mar 2026 18:05:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] ports/rp2: power-cycle CYW43 on soft reset

After fixing the rp2 BTstack run loop and HCI scheduler state, Polar H10
PSFTP pairing became reliable after hard reset, but could still regress
across repeated MicroPython soft-reset cycles.

On rp2, cyw43_state is initialised once at power-up and survives
interpreter soft resets. With lwIP enabled, mod_network_deinit() does not
deinitialise CYW43 on soft reset, and the BTstack shutdown path also does
not power-cycle the shared CYW43 Wi-Fi/Bluetooth device.

That leaves the CYW43 shared-bus Bluetooth side warm across interpreter
lifetimes, which can preserve stale controller/bus state and correlates
with SMP pairing stalling again on the next run.

Reset the CYW43 device during rp2 soft reset, after Bluetooth deinit has
completed. cyw43_deinit() powers the chip down and reinitialises driver
state, giving the next interpreter instance a clean controller state
without requiring a physical reset.

---
 ports/rp2/main.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/ports/rp2/main.c b/ports/rp2/main.c
index 7788d820f..9a79e7209 100644
--- a/ports/rp2/main.c
+++ b/ports/rp2/main.c
@@ -258,6 +258,9 @@ soft_reset_exit:
         #if MICROPY_PY_BLUETOOTH
         mp_bluetooth_deinit();
         #endif
+        #if MICROPY_PY_BLUETOOTH_CYW43
+        cyw43_deinit(&cyw43_state);
+        #endif
         #if MICROPY_PY_MACHINE_PWM
         machine_pwm_deinit_all();
         #endif
